&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Brief Description of the Role: &lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is an excellent opportunity to work as part of the Orthoptic team based at Bradford Royal Infirmary.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Roles and responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;: To provide clinical leadership to the Low Vision service and line management of the orthoptic clerk.This role will also be involved in the provision of orthoptic support for general ophthalmology, paediatric ophthalmology and maxillo-facial services.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Bradford Teaching Hospitals NHS Foundation Trust is an approved site for orthoptic student placements and the post holder will be required to be an active member of the clinical tutoring provided.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Regular Clinical Governance/audit sessions are held and active participation is encouraged by all staff. We also support the mentoring process for any new staff. We are a progressive department keen to support and develop our staff.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Experience/Skills/Qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;required: E&lt;/strong&gt;xperience of working at an advanced level in orthoptics and low vision is essential.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Informal Enquiries to: &lt;/strong&gt;Stephanie MindhamHead Orthoptist on 01274 383167.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We can offer staff gymnasiums on both hospital sites, excellent pension scheme and advice on childcare.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Closing Date:06.11.20 (This date may change dependent on the response)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
